comments: Barnes (SAC) splits his pivot foot prior to the start of his drive.
Jokic (DEN) makes contact to the body of Barnes (SAC) during his shooting motion that disrupts his driving shot attempt.

Replay review of the foul called on Murray (DEN) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Murray cups Whiteside's (SAC) side, who is making a legal attempt to block the shot, and there is no clear and conclusive evidence to overturn the call on the floor.
Millsap (DEN) makes contact to the arm of Whiteside (SAC) during his shooting motion that disrupts his play at the basket.
Hield (SAC) wraps the upper body of Jokic (DEN) while trying to defend around the screen being set.
Harris (DEN) makes marginal two hand contact to Fox's (SAC) body as he receives the inbound pass.
Jokic (DEN) uses both hands and pushes Joseph (SAC) while setting the pick. Disrupting his ability to defend.
Whiteside (SAC) makes contact to Jokic's (DEN) wrist/arm that causes him to lose possession of the ball.
Whiteside (SAC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Barton (DEN) firms up and absorbs the contact.
Porter Jr. (DEN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Fox (SAC) after the release that does not affect his shot attempt.
Hield (SAC) makes marginal contact to Porter Jr's (DEN) body during his layup attempt, and does not disrupts his shooting motion.
Whiteside (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Jokic (DEN).
Barton (DEN) makes marginal contact to Barnes' (SAC) body as he gathers and enters his shooting motion.
Whiteside (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position as Barton (DEN) initiates the contact during his driving shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) grabs the rim when the ball is outside of the cylinder.
Fox (SAC) makes marginal contact with Barton (DEN) when he makes the pass.
Joseph (SAC) commits a take foul on Harris (DEN).
Fox (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Barton (DEN) and cleanly blocks the dunk.
Barnes (SAC) takes more than two steps after gathering the ball.
Barnes (SAC) makes contact to Jokic's (DEN) arms as he receives the inbound pass and causes him to lose possession of the ball.
Barton (DEN) jumps from point A to point B into Barnes (SAC) and makes contact with his arm and body that affect the dunk attempt.
